---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import DatePickerComponent from '../../components/DatePicker.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import { DatePicker } from 'comet-astro';

---

<div class="space-y-6">
  <DatePicker 
    label="Start date" 
    placeholder="Choose your start date"
    value="2024-01-15"
  />
  <DatePicker 
    label="Event date" 
    min="2024-01-01"
    max="2024-12-31"
    firstDayOfWeek={1}
    showTodayShortcut={true}
  />
</div>`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="DatePicker"
  description="Accessible calendar picker with WCAG AAA contrast, keyboard navigation, and date range constraints."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      DatePicker provides an intuitive calendar interface for date selection with full keyboard navigation support 
      and fast year/month navigation. The component maintains WCAG AAA contrast ratios across all interactive 
      elements and states, ensuring accessibility for users with varying visual capabilities.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Calendar navigation includes clickable month/year headers for rapid date switching, month traversal with 
      dedicated year jump buttons, date range constraints, and customizable week start days. Focus management 
      follows modern accessibility patterns with clear visual indicators and screen reader support.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          value?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Initial selected date in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> format. Updates hidden input for form submission.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          label?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Accessible label text for the date input. Defaults to <code>"Select date"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          placeholder?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Placeholder text shown when no date is selected. Defaults to <code>"Choose a date"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          min?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Minimum selectable date in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> format. Dates before this are disabled.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          max?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Maximum selectable date in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> format. Dates after this are disabled.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          firstDayOfWeek?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          First day of the week (0=Sunday, 1=Monday, etc.). Defaults to <code>1</code> (Monday).
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          inputName?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Name attribute for the hidden input field, enabling form submission integration.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          showTodayShortcut?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Shows "Today" button for quick current date selection. Defaults to <code>true</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm sm:col-span-2"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          className?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Additional CSS classes to apply to the outer container for custom styling.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Import the component and configure date constraints, labels, and calendar behavior. 
      The component handles keyboard navigation, focus management, and form integration automatically.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{usageSnippet}</code>
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Basic Example</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      A simple date picker with default configuration and responsive design.
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-sm">
      <DatePickerComponent label="Schedule start date" placeholder="Select a date" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">With Date Range</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Constrain selectable dates to a specific range using min and max properties.
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-sm">
      <DatePickerComponent 
        label="Event date" 
        placeholder="Choose event date"
        min="2024-01-01"
        max="2024-12-31"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Week Configuration</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Customize the first day of the week and disable the Today shortcut for specific use cases.
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-sm">
      <DatePickerComponent 
        label="Week start Sunday" 
        placeholder="Select date"
        firstDayOfWeek={0}
        showTodayShortcut={false}
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Fast Navigation</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Click month or year headers to quickly jump between months and years. Use the double arrows for year-by-year navigation.
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-sm">
      <DatePickerComponent 
        label="Fast navigation example" 
        placeholder="Try clicking month/year"
        min="2020-01-01"
        max="2030-12-31"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Historical Date Range</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Test with historical dates from 1990s era to verify range constraints work across decades.
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-sm">
      <DatePickerComponent 
        label="Birth date (1990s)" 
        placeholder="Select birth date"
        min="1990-01-01"
        max="1999-12-31"
        value="1995-06-15"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Form Integration</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Include an input name for seamless form submission with hidden input handling.
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-sm">
      <DatePickerComponent 
        label="Birth date" 
        placeholder="Enter your birth date"
        inputName="birthDate"
        value="1990-01-01"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Contrast ratios exceed WCAG AAA requirements (7:1+) across all calendar elements, date cells, 
      and navigation controls in both light and dark themes. Focus indicators use 2px visible rings 
      with theme-aware offsets for clear keyboard navigation tracking.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Calendar navigation supports full keyboard control: arrow keys for date navigation, 
      Enter/Space for selection, Escape to close (or return from month/year picker), and Tab to cycle through 
      interactive elements. Screen readers receive proper ARIA labels, role assignments, and state announcements.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Fast navigation is accessible via clickable month/year headers that open dedicated picker dialogs. 
      Year navigation includes « » buttons for rapid year jumping, and date range constraints are properly 
      enforced across all navigation modes to prevent selection of invalid dates.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The calendar dialog maintains focus trap behavior when open, and returns focus to the 
      trigger button when closed. Date ranges and constraints are clearly communicated to 
      assistive technologies through semantic markup and ARIA attributes.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
